OL,5,FThe defence argued it was impossible
OL,6,Fto determine how he died due to
OL,7,Fdecomposition.
OL,9,FThe Judge told the court he was
OL,10,Fsatisfied this was a "murderous,
OL,11,Fferocious," knife attack. That Mr
OL,12,FHeagney died of multiple stab wounds
OL,13,Fto the head.
OL,15,FHe also rejected any suggestion that
OL,16,Fsomeone else was involved as there was
OL,17,F"no credible or reliable evidence of a
OL,18,Fthird party".
OL,20,FMr Heagney's family said the actions
OL,21,Fthat led to his death were "depraved".
