OL,5,F"It's actually impossible to stop
OL,6,Fthinking about what happened to
OL,7,FDamien. We go over it, again and
OL,8,Fagain, and it haunts us.
OL,10,F"Yet, among the torment, we've each
OL,11,Ftaken comfort from the genuine
OL,12,Fkindness and support shown by others.
OL,14,F"We would like to thank the jury who
OL,15,Fput in so much time and effort,
OL,16,Flistening to all the evidence to bring
OL,17,Fback a guilty verdict, especially in
OL,18,Fsuch a difficult case. We will always
OL,19,Fbe grateful to them."
